#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1709
#, lua-format
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, this mine can produce gold ore in %s on "
"average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, ši kasykla gali pagaminti vidutiniškai %s aukso rūdos."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle Arena
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1718
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘No better friend you have in battle than the enemy’s blow that misses.’"
msgstr "„Nėra geresnio draugo mūšyje, nei priešo smūgis, kurio nepastebėta“."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle
#. Arena
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1720
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Said to originate from Neidhardt, the famous trainer."
msgstr "Teigiama, kad kilęs iš Neidhardto, garsaus trenerio."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle Arena,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1723
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Trains soldiers in ‘Evade’."
msgstr "Treniruoja karius „Evade“."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle Arena,
#. part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1725
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘Evade’ increases the soldier’s chance not to be hit by the enemy and so to "
"remain totally unaffected."
msgstr "„Evade“ padidina kareivio galimybę nenukentėti priešo ir likti visiškai nepakitusiam."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle Arena
#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian building: Training Camp
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1728
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1751
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"Barbarian soldiers cannot be trained in ‘Defense’ and will remain at their "
"initial level."
msgstr "Barbarų kariai negali būti mokomi „gynybos“ ir išliks pradiniame lygyje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle
#. Arena, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1731
#, lua-format
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"If all needed wares are delivered in time, a battle arena can train one "
"soldier one level in evade in %s on average."
msgstr "Jei visi reikalingi gaminiai pristatomi laiku, mūšio arena gali išmokyti vieną kareivį vienu lygiu, kad būtų išvengta vidutiniškai %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian training site: Battle
#. Arena, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian training site: Training
#. Camp, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1733
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1756
#, lua-format
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Complete training of one soldier takes %s on average."
msgstr "Visiškas vieno kario mokymas vidutiniškai užtrunka %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian training site: Training Camp
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1741
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘He who is strong shall neither forgive nor forget, but revenge injustice "
"suffered – in the past and for all future.’"
msgstr "„Tas, kuris yra stiprus, nei atleis, nei pamirš, bet kerštas už neteisybę – praeityje ir už visą ateitį“."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian training site: Training
#. Camp
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1743
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Chief Chat’Karuth in a speech to his army."
msgstr "Vyriausiasis Chat'karuthas kalboje savo armijai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian training site: Training Camp,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1746
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Trains soldiers in ‘Attack’ and in ‘Health’."
msgstr "Apmoko karius „ataka“ ir „sveikata“."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian training site: Training Camp,
#. part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1748
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Equips the soldiers with all necessary weapons and armor parts."
msgstr "aprūpina karius visais reikalingais ginklais ir šarvų dalimis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian training site: Training
#. Camp, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1754
#, lua-format
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"If all needed wares are delivered in time, a training camp can train one "
"soldier one level in attack or health in %s on average."
msgstr "Jei visi reikalingi gaminiai pristatomi laiku, treniruočių stovykla gali išmokyti vieną karį vieno lygio puolimo ar sveikatos vidutiniškai %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Sentry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1766
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘The log cabin was so small that two men could hardly live there. But we "
"were young and carefree. We just relished our freedom and the responsibility"
" as an outpost.’"
msgstr "„Rąstinis namelis buvo toks mažas, kad ten sunkiai galėjo gyventi du vyrai. Bet mes buvome jauni ir nerūpestingi. Mes tiesiog mėgavomės savo laisve ir atsakomybe kaip forpostu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian military site: Sentry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1768
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Boldreth,<br>about his time as young soldier"
msgstr "Boldreth,<br>apie savo, kaip jauno kareivio, laiką"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian military site: Sentry
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian military site: Barrier
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian military site: Tower
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian military site: Fortress
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian military site: Citadel
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1770
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1783
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1797
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1810
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1823
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Garrisons soldiers to expand your territory."
msgstr "Garnizonų kariai, kad išplėstų jūsų teritoriją."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian military site: Sentry
#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian military site: Barrier
#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian military site: Tower
#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian military site: Fortress
#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Barbarian military site: Citadel
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1772
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1785
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1799
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1812
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1825
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"If you’re low on soldiers to occupy new military sites, use the downward "
"arrow button to decrease the capacity. You can also click on a soldier to "
"send him away."
msgstr "Jei jums trūksta kareivių, kad galėtumėte užimti naujas karines vietas, naudokite rodyklės žemyn mygtuką, kad sumažintumėte pajėgumus. Taip pat galite spustelėti kareivį, kad jį išsiųstumėte."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Barrier
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1779
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘When we looked down to the valley from our newly established barrier, we "
"felt that the spirit of our fathers was with us.’"
msgstr "„Kai pažvelgėme į slėnį iš naujai įsteigto barjero, pajutome, kad mūsų tėvų dvasia yra su mumis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Tower
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1793
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘From the height of our tower we could see far into enemy territory. The "
"enemy was well prepared, but we also noticed some weak points in their "
"defense.’"
msgstr "„Nuo mūsų bokšto aukščio matėme toli į priešo teritoriją. Priešas buvo gerai pasiruošęs, bet pastebėjome ir kai kurias silpnąsias jų gynybos vietas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Fortress
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1806
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘This stronghold made from blackwood and stones will be a hard nut to crack "
"for them.’"
msgstr "„Ši tvirtovė, pagaminta iš juodmedžio ir akmenų, jiems bus kietas riešutas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian military site: Fortress
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1808
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Berthron,<br>chief military adviser of Chat’Karuth"
msgstr "Berthronas, Chat'Karuth vyriausiasis karinis patarėjas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Citadel
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1819
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘The Citadel of Adlen surely is the finest masterpiece of Barbarian "
"craftsmanship. Nothing as strong and big and beautiful has ever been built "
"in such a short time.’"
msgstr "„Adleno citadelė tikrai yra geriausias barbarų meistriškumo šedevras. Niekas tokio stipraus, didelio ir gražaus nebuvo pastatytas per tokį trumpą laiką."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian military site: Citadel
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1821
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"Colintan, chief planner of the Citadel of Adlen,<br>at its opening ceremony"
msgstr "Colintanas, Adleno citadelės vyriausiasis planuotojas,<br>jos atidarymo ceremonijoje"

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian production site: Ferry
#. Yard, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1843
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one ferry between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the shipwright has to walk."
msgstr "Šis pastatas gali nutiesti vieną keltą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli laivų meistras turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian production site: Shipyard
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1853
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘When I saw the Saxnot for the first time, her majestic dragon head already "
"looked up to the skies and the master was about to install the square "
"sail.<br>It was the most noble ship I ever saw.’"
msgstr "„Kai pirmą kartą pamačiau saksotą, jos didinga drakono galva jau pažvelgė į dangų ir šeimininkas ruošėsi įrengti kvadratinę burę.<br>Tai buvo pats kilniausias laivas, kokį aš kada nors mačiau."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian production site:
#. Shipyard, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1867
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one ship between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the shipwright has to walk."
msgstr "Šis pastatas gali pagaminti vieną laivą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli turi nueiti laivų meistras."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian production site: Weaving Mill
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1877
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"‘Fine cloth and jewelry mean nothing to a true Barbarian.<br>But a noble "
"sail in the wind will please his eyes.’"
msgstr "„Tikram barbarui puikus audinys ir papuošalai nieko nereiškia.<br>Bet kilni burė vėjyje džiugins jo akis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian production site: Weaving
#. Mill
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1880
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid ""
"Khantarakh, ‘The Modern Barbarian Economy’,<br>9ᵗʰ cowhide ‘Seafaring and "
"Conquest’"
msgstr "Khantarakhas, „Šiuolaikinė barbarų ekonomika“,<br>9ᵗʰ karvės oda „jūriniai ir užkariavimai“"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Barbarian production site: Weaving Mill
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1882
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "Weaves cloth out of reed."
msgstr "Iš nendrių audžia audinį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Barbarian production site: Weaving
#. Mill
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/barbarians/units.lua:1884
#, lua-format
msgctxt "barbarians_building"
msgid "The weaving mill needs %s on average to produce one cloth."
msgstr "Audimo malūnui vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad pagamintų vieną audinį."

