#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Log, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:99
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Woodcutters fell the trees; foresters take care of the supply of trees. Logs"
" are also used in the blacksmithy to build basic tools, and in the charcoal "
"kiln for the production of coal. Smokeries use logs as fuel for smoking meat"
" and fish."
msgstr "Medkirtys nuvertė medžius; Miškininkai rūpinasi medžių tiekimu. Rąstai taip pat naudojami kalvystėje gaminant pagrindinius įrankius, o anglies krosnyje – anglies gamybai. Rūkaliai naudoja rąstus kaip mėsos ir žuvies rūkymo kurą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Granite, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:112
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"The Frisians produce granite blocks in quarries and rock mines. They can be "
"refined in a brick kiln."
msgstr "Fryzai gamina granito blokus karjeruose ir uolienų kasyklose. Juos galima rafinuoti plytų krosnyje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Clay
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:122
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Clay is made out of water and mud to be turned into bricks, used in ship "
"construction and to improve the charcoal kiln."
msgstr "Molis gaminamas iš vandens ir purvo, kuris paverčiamas plytomis, naudojamas laivų statyboje ir anglies krosnies gerinimui."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Brick
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:131
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Bricks are the best and most important building material. They are made out "
"of a mix of clay and granite dried in a coal fire."
msgstr "Plytos yra geriausia ir svarbiausia statybinė medžiaga. Jie gaminami iš molio ir granito mišinio, džiovinto anglies ugnyje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Reed
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:139
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Reed is grown in a reed farm. Nothing is better suited to make roofs "
"waterproof. It is also used to make baskets and fishing nets as well as "
"cloth."
msgstr "Nendrės auginamos nendrių ūkyje. Nieko nėra geriau, kad stogai būtų atsparūs vandeniui. Jis taip pat naudojamas krepšiams ir žvejybos tinklams bei audiniams gaminti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Fur
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:148
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Fur is won from reindeer in a reindeer farm. It is woven into cloth or "
"turned into fur garments for soldiers."
msgstr "Kailis laimi iš šiaurės elnių šiaurės elnių fermoje. Jis austas į audinį arba paverčiamas kailiniais drabužiais kareiviams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Cloth
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:157
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Cloth is needed for ships. It is produced out of reindeer fur and reed."
msgstr "Audinys reikalingas laivams. Jis gaminamas iš šiaurės elnių kailio ir nendrių."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Fruit
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:168
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Fruit are berries gathered from berry bushes by a fruit collector. They are "
"used for rations and for feeding the fish at the aqua farms."
msgstr "Vaisiai – tai vaisių kolekcionieriaus iš uogų krūmų surinktos uogos. Jie naudojami racionui ir žuvims šerti vandens fermose."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Water, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:179
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Water is used to bake bread and brew beer. Reindeer farms and aqua farms "
"also consume it."
msgstr "Vanduo naudojamas duonai kepti ir alui virti. Jį taip pat vartoja šiaurės elnių ūkiai ir vandens ūkiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Barley
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:188
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Barley is a slow-growing grain that is used for baking bread and brewing "
"beer. It is also eaten by reindeer."
msgstr "Miežiai – tai lėtai augantis grūdas, naudojamas duonai kepti ir alaus gamybai. Jį taip pat valgo šiaurės elniai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Honey
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:196
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Honey is produced by bees belonging to a beekeeper. It is used to bake honey"
" bread and brew mead."
msgstr "Medų gamina bitės, priklausančios bitininkui. Jis naudojamas medaus duonos ir midaus virimui."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Bread
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:205
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Bread is made out of barley and water and is used in the taverns to prepare "
"rations. It is also consumed by training soldiers."
msgstr "Duona gaminama iš miežių ir vandens ir naudojama smuklėse racionui ruošti. Jį taip pat suvartoja besimokantys kariai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Honey Bread
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:214
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"This bread is sweetened with honey. It is consumed by the most experienced "
"miners and in advanced soldier training."
msgstr "Ši duona pasaldinta medumi. Jį vartoja labiausiai patyrę kalnakasiai ir pažangių karių mokyme."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Beer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:223
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Beer is produced in breweries and used in drinking halls to produce meals. "
"Soldiers drink beer while receiving basic training."
msgstr "Alus gaminamas alaus daryklose ir naudojamas gėrimo salėse patiekalams gaminti. Kareiviai geria alų gaudami pagrindinius mokymus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Mead
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:232
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Mead is produced by mead breweries. Soldiers drink mead during advanced "
"training."
msgstr "Midus gamina Mead Breweries. Kareiviai geria midų per išplėstines treniruotes."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Fish
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:241
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Fish is a very important food resource for the Frisians. It is fished from "
"the shore or reared in aqua farms."
msgstr "Žuvis yra labai svarbus fryzų maisto šaltinis. Jis žvejojamas iš kranto arba auginamas vandens fermose."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Meat, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:252
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Meat has to be smoked in a smokery before being delivered to taverns, "
"drinking halls and training sites."
msgstr "Mėsa turi būti rūkoma rūkykloje prieš pristatoma į smukles, gėrimo sales ir mokymo vietas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Smoked Fish
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:262
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Fish is smoked in a smokery. Smoked fish is then consumed by soldiers in "
"training or turned into rations and meals for miners and scouts."
msgstr "Žuvis rūkoma rūkykloje. Tada rūkytą žuvį vartoja kariai treniruotėse arba paverčia racionu ir patiekalais kalnakasiams ir skautams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Smoked Meat
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:271
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Meat is smoked in a smokery. Smoked meat is then consumed by soldiers in "
"training or turned into rations and meals for miners and scouts."
msgstr "Mėsa rūkoma rūkykloje. Tada rūkytą mėsą vartoja kariai treniruotėse arba paverčia racionu ir patiekalais kalnakasiams ir skautams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Ration, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:283
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Rations are produced in taverns and drinking halls out of something to eat: "
"Fruit, bread or smoked meat or fish."
msgstr "Racionai gaminami smuklėse ir gėrimo salėse iš ko nors valgyti: vaisių, duonos ar rūkytos mėsos ar žuvies."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Meal
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:293
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"A meal is made out of honey bread and beer and either smoked fish or meat. "
"It is consumed by miners in deep mines."
msgstr "Patiekalas gaminamas iš medaus duonos ir alaus bei rūkytos žuvies arba mėsos. Jį vartoja kalnakasiai giliose kasyklose."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Coal, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:306
msgctxt "ware"
msgid ""
"Coal is mined in coal mines or produced out of logs by a charcoal burner in "
"a charcoal kiln or charcoal burner’s house."
msgstr "Anglis kasama anglies kasyklose arba gaminama iš rąstų anglies degikliu anglies krosnyje arba anglies degiklio name."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Coal, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:308
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"The fires of the brick kilns, furnaces, armor smithies and recycling centers"
" are fed with coal."
msgstr "Mūrinių krosnių, krosnių, šarvų kalvių ir perdirbimo centrų gaisrai maitinami anglimi."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Iron Ore, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:321
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "It is smelted in a furnace to retrieve the iron."
msgstr "Jis išlydomas krosnyje, kad paimtų geležį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Iron, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:334
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"It is produced by the furnace. Tools and weapons are made of iron. It is "
"also used as jewellery for fur garment armor to give it a silver shine."
msgstr "Jį gamina krosnis. Įrankiai ir ginklai pagaminti iš geležies. Jis taip pat naudojamas kaip kailinių drabužių šarvų papuošalas, suteikiantis sidabro blizgesio."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Gold Ore, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:347
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Smelted in a furnace, it turns into gold which is used as a precious "
"building material and to produce weapons and armor."
msgstr "Išlydytas krosnyje, jis virsta auksu, kuris naudojamas kaip brangi statybinė medžiaga ir gamina ginklus bei šarvus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Gold, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:360
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Only very important things are embellished with gold. It is produced by the "
"furnace and is used to produce better swords and the best helmets. The best "
"armor is also decorated with gold."
msgstr "Tik labai svarbūs daiktai papuošti auksu. Jis gaminamas iš krosnies ir naudojamas geresniems kardams ir geriausiems šalmams gaminti. Geriausi šarvai taip pat papuošti auksu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Scrap Iron
#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Scrap metal (mixed)
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:369
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:377
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Discarded weapons and armor can be recycled in a recycling center to produce"
" new tools, weapon and armor."
msgstr "Išmestus ginklus ir šarvus galima perdirbti perdirbimo centre, kad būtų pagaminti nauji įrankiai, ginklai ir šarvai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Old Fur Garment
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:385
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Old garments can be turned into fur in a recycling center."
msgstr "Senus drabužius galima paversti kailiu perdirbimo centre."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Pick
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:397
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Picks are used by stonemasons and miners."
msgstr "Picks naudoja akmentašiai ir kalnakasiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Felling Ax, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:409
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Felling axes are used by woodcutters and produced by the blacksmithy."
msgstr "Kirti kirvius naudoja medžio kirtėjai, o gamina kalvė."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Shovel, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:422
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"They are used by berry and reed farmers as well as foresters. Clay diggers "
"also need them to dig mud out of hard soil."
msgstr "Juos naudoja uogų ir nendrių augintojai, taip pat miškininkai. Molio kasėjams jų taip pat reikia, kad iš kieto dirvožemio kastų purvą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Hammer, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:435
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Geologists, builders, blacksmiths and shipwrights all need a hammer. Make "
"sure you’ve always got some in reserve! They are produced by the "
"blacksmithy."
msgstr "Geologams, statybininkams, kalviams ir laivų meistrams reikia plaktuko. Įsitikinkite, kad visada turite atsargų! Juos gamina kalvė."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Fishing Net
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:445
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Fishing nets are the tool used by fishers."
msgstr "Žvejybos tinklai yra žvejų naudojamas įrankis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Hunting Spear, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:457
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Hunting spears are produced by the blacksmithy"
msgstr "Medžioklės ietis gamina kalvė"

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Scythe, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:470
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Scythes are produced by the blacksmithy."
msgstr "dalgius gamina kalvė."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Bread Paddle, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:483
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Bread paddles are produced by the blacksmithy."
msgstr "Duonos irklas gamina kalvė."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Kitchen Tools
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:493
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Kitchen tools are needed for preparing rations and meals. The smoker also "
"needs them."
msgstr "Virtuviniai įrankiai reikalingi racionui ir patiekalams ruošti. Rūkaliui jų taip pat reikia."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Fire Tongs, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:505
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"They are used in the furnace and the brick kiln and produced by the "
"blacksmithy."
msgstr "Jie naudojami krosnyje ir plytų krosnyje ir gamina kalvystės."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Basket
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:515
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Baskets are needed by the fruit collector to gather berries. They are woven "
"from reed and wood by the blacksmith."
msgstr "Vaisių kolekcionieriui uogoms rinkti reikia krepšelių. Juos iš nendrių ir medžio austi kalvis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Needles
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:524
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid "Needles are used by seamstresses to sew cloth and fur garments."
msgstr "Adatos siuvėjos naudoja audiniams ir kailiniams drabužiams siūti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Short sword
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:536
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"This is the basic weapon of the Frisian soldiers. Together with a fur "
"garment, it makes up the equipment of young soldiers. Short swords are "
"produced by the small armor smithy."
msgstr "Tai yra pagrindinis fryzų karių ginklas. Kartu su kailiniu drabužiu jis sudaro jaunų kareivių įrangą. Trumpus kardus gamina mažoji šarvų kalvė."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Long Sword
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:545
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"The long sword is the weapon used by level 1 soldiers. Level 4 soldiers are "
"equipped with a long and a double-edged sword."
msgstr "Ilgas kardas yra 1 lygio kareivių naudojamas ginklas. 4 lygio kariai aprūpinti ilgu ir dviašmeniu kardu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Broadsword
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:554
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"The broadsword is the weapon used by level 2 soldiers. Level 5 soldiers are "
"equipped with a broadsword and a double-edged sword."
msgstr "Platus kardas yra 2 lygio karių naudojamas ginklas. 5 lygio kariai aprūpinti plačiu kardu ir dviašmeniu kardu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Double-edged Sword
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:563
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"The double-edged sword is the weapon used by level 3 soldiers. Level 6 "
"soldiers are equipped with two of these ferocious swords."
msgstr "Dviašmenis kardas yra 3 lygio karių naudojamas ginklas. 6 lygio kariai aprūpinti dviem iš šių žiaurių kardų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Fur Garment
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:572
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Fur can be sewn into garments. They are used as basic armor. All new "
"soldiers are clothed in a fur garment."
msgstr "Kailį galima siūti į drabužius. Jie naudojami kaip pagrindiniai šarvai. Visi nauji kariai apsirengę kailiniu drabužiu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Studded Fur Garment
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:581
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Ordinary fur garments can be decorated with iron to give them a silvery "
"shine. These clothes make good armor."
msgstr "Įprastus kailinius drabužius galima papuošti geležimi, kad jie įgautų sidabrinį blizgesį. Šie drabužiai yra geri šarvai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Golden Fur Garment
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:590
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"Ordinary fur garments can be decorated with iron and gold. Such clothes are "
"the best armor."
msgstr "Įprastus kailinius drabužius galima papuošti geležimi ir auksu. Tokie drabužiai yra geriausi šarvai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Helmet
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:599
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"A helmet is a basic tool to protect soldiers. It is produced in the small "
"armor smithy and used to train soldiers from health level 0 to level 1."
msgstr "Šalmas yra pagrindinė karių apsaugos priemonė. Jis gaminamas mažoje šarvų kalvėje ir naudojamas kariams mokyti nuo 0 iki 1 lygio."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian ware: Golden Helmet
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:608
msgctxt "frisians_ware"
msgid ""
"A golden helmet protects soldiers. It is produced in the large armor smithy "
"and used to train soldiers from health level 1 to level 2."
msgstr "Auksinis šalmas apsaugo karius. Jis gaminamas didelėje šarvų kalvėje ir naudojamas kariams mokyti nuo 1 iki 2 lygio."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Carrier
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:624
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Carries items along your roads."
msgstr "neša daiktus savo keliais."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Ferry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:631
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Ships wares across narrow rivers."
msgstr "Laivai veža dirbinius per siauras upes."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Reindeer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:640
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid ""
"Reindeer help to carry items along busy roads. They are reared in a reindeer"
" farm."
msgstr "Šiaurės elniai padeda neštis daiktus judriais keliais. Jie auginami šiaurės elnių ūkyje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Reindeer Breeder
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:647
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Breeds reindeer as carriers and for their fur."
msgstr "Veisia šiaurės elnius kaip nešiotojai ir jų kailiui."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Stonemason
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:657
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Cuts raw pieces of granite out of rocks in the vicinity."
msgstr "Pjauna neapdorotus granito gabalus iš netoliese esančių uolų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Woodcutter
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:664
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Fells trees."
msgstr "Fells medžiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Forester
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:671
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Plants trees."
msgstr "Augalų medžius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Clay Digger
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:678
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Makes clay out of mud and water."
msgstr "Padaro molį iš purvo ir vandens."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Brickmaker
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:685
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Burns bricks out of clay and granite."
msgstr "Dega plytas iš molio ir granito."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Builder
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:692
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Works at construction sites to raise new buildings."
msgstr "Statybose dirba nauji pastatai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Gardener
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:699
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Plants and harvests reed fields."
msgstr "Augalai ir derliaus nendrių laukai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Seamstress
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:706
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Produces cloth and sews fur garments."
msgstr "Gamina audinį ir siuva kailinius drabužius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Master Seamstress
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:713
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Sews armor out of fur garments and metal."
msgstr "Iš kailinių drabužių ir metalo siuva šarvus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Shipwright
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:720
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Works at the shipyard and constructs new ships."
msgstr "Dirba laivų statykloje ir stato naujus laivus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian worker: Diker
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:727
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Constructs breakwaters to gain new land from the sea."
msgstr "Stato molą, kad iš jūros įgytų naują žemę."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Fisher
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:737
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Catches fish in the sea."
msgstr "gaudo žuvis jūroje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Hunter
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:744
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "The hunter brings fresh, raw meat to the colonists."
msgstr "Medžiotojas kolonistams atneša šviežios, žalios mėsos."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Farmer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:751
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Plants fields."
msgstr "Augalų laukai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Berry Farmer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:758
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Plants berry bushes."
msgstr "Augalų uogų krūmai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Fruit Collector
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:765
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Gathers berries."
msgstr "renka uogas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Smoker
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:772
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Refines meat and fish by smoking them."
msgstr "Rafinuoja mėsą ir žuvį rūkant."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Beekeeper
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:779
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Lets bees swarm over flowers, then gathers the honey."
msgstr "Leiskite bitėms knibždėti ant gėlių, tada surenka medų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Baker
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:786
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Bakes bread for miners and soldiers."
msgstr "Kepa duoną kalnakasiams ir kariams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Master Baker
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:793
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "This baker is skilled enough to bake bread sweetened with honey."
msgstr "Šis kepėjas yra pakankamai įgudęs kepti medumi pasaldintą duoną."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Brewer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:800
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Brews beer."
msgstr "gamina alų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Master Brewer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:807
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Brews beer and mead."
msgstr "gamina alų ir midaus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Landlady
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:814
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Prepares rations and meals for miners and scouts."
msgstr "Ruošia davinius ir patiekalus kalnakasiams ir skautams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Geologist
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:824
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Discovers resources for mining."
msgstr "Atranda išteklių kasybai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Miner
#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Master Miner
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:831
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:838
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Works deep in the mines to obtain coal, iron, gold or granite."
msgstr "Dirba giliai kasyklose, kad gautų anglies, geležies, aukso ar granito."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Charcoal Burner
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:845
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Burns logs and clay to produce coal."
msgstr "Sudegina rąstus ir molį anglims gaminti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Smelter
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:852
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Smelts iron and gold at furnaces or recycling centers."
msgstr "Krosnyse arba perdirbimo centruose lydo geležis ir auksas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Blacksmith
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:859
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Produces weapons and armor for soldiers and tools for workers."
msgstr "Gamina ginklus ir šarvus kariams ir įrankius darbininkams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Master Blacksmith
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:866
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid ""
"Produces the best weapons and armor for soldiers and tools for workers."
msgstr "Gamina geriausius ginklus ir šarvus kariams ir įrankius darbuotojams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Soldier
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:878
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Defend and Conquer!"
msgstr "Ginkitės ir užkariaukite!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Trainer
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:885
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Trains the soldiers."
msgstr "treniruoja karius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian worker: Scout
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:892
msgctxt "frisians_worker"
msgid "Explores unknown territory."
msgstr "tyrinėja nežinomą teritoriją."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: One of the berry bushes
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:917
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:945
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:973
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1001
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1029
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1057
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1085
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1113
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1141
msgid "This berry bush has just been planted."
msgstr "Šis uogų krūmas ką tik pasodintas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: One of the berry bushes
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:924
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:952
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:980
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1008
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1036
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1064
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1092
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1120
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1148
msgid "This berry bush is growing."
msgstr "Šis uogų krūmas auga."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: One of the berry bushes
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:931
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:959
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:987
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1015
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1043
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1071
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1099
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1127
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1155
msgid ""
"This berry bush is flowering. Honey can be produced from it by a beekeeper."
msgstr "Šis uogų krūmas žydi. Iš jo medų gali gaminti bitininkas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: One of the berry bushes
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:938
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:966
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:994
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1022
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1050
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1078
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1106
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1134
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1162
msgid "This berry bush is ready for harvesting."
msgstr "Šis uogų krūmas paruoštas derliui."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Barley Field
#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for an Empire/Barbarian immovable usable by Frisians:
#. Wheat field
#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a an Atlantean immovable usable by Frisians: Corn
#. Field
#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for an Atlantean immovable usable by Frisians:
#. Blackroot Field
#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for an Amazon immovable usable by Frisians: Cassava
#. field
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1183
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1387
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1394
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1401
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1415
msgid "This field is flowering. Honey can be produced from it by a beekeeper."
msgstr "Šis laukas žydi. Iš jo medų gali gaminti bitininkas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Pond
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1204
msgid ""
"When claydiggers dig up earth, they leave holes in the ground. These holes "
"vanish after a while. Aqua farms can use them as ponds to grow fish in them,"
" whereas charcoal burners erect their charcoal stacks in them."
msgstr "Kai Claydiggers kasa žemę, jie palieka skyles žemėje. Šios skylės po kurio laiko išnyksta. „Aqua Farms“ gali juos naudoti kaip tvenkinius žuvims auginti, o anglies degikliai juose stato anglies krūvas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Pond
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1211
msgid ""
"Fish are maturing in this pond. A fisher working from an aqua farm will be "
"able to catch them when they are bigger."
msgstr "Šiame tvenkinyje bręsta žuvys. Vandens fermoje dirbantis žvejys galės juos sugauti, kai jie bus didesni."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Pond
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1218
msgid ""
"Fish are living in this pond. A fisher working from an aqua farm can catch "
"them as food."
msgstr "Šiame tvenkinyje gyvena žuvys. Žvejas, dirbantis iš vandens ūkio, gali juos pagauti kaip maistą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Pond
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1225
msgid ""
"A charcoal stack is burning in this earthen hole. When it has burnt down, a "
"charcoal burner will be able to gather coal from it."
msgstr "Šioje molinėje skylėje dega anglies kaminas. Kai jis sudegs, anglies degiklis galės iš jo surinkti anglį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Pond
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1232
msgid ""
"A charcoal stack, which had been erected in this earthen hole, is ready for "
"a charcoal burner to gather coal from it."
msgstr "Šioje molinėje duobėje pastatyta anglies krūva yra paruošta anglies degikliui, kad iš jos surinktų anglį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Dike
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1239
msgid "A breakwater erected by a diker to gain new land from the sea."
msgstr "moras, kurį pastatė pypsėjimas, siekiant gauti naują žemę iš jūros."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Diker's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1241
msgid ""
"You can manually remove the dike when the land is sufficiently secured to "
"prevent wasting resources. To do so, build a flag, road, or building in its "
"place."
msgstr "Galite rankiniu būdu išimti pylimą, kai žemė yra pakankamai apsaugota, kad būtų išvengta išteklių švaistymo. Norėdami tai padaryti, vietoj jo pastatykite vėliavą, kelią ar pastatą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian immovable: Reed Field
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1262
msgid ""
"This reed field is flowering. Honey can be produced from it by a beekeeper."
msgstr "Šis nendrių laukas žydi. Iš jo medų gali gaminti bitininkas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for a Frisian resource indicator: Stones, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1324
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1368
msgid "Granite is a basic building material and can be dug up by a rock mine."
msgstr "Granitas yra pagrindinė statybinė medžiaga, kurią galima iškasti uolų kasykloje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Helptext for an Empire immovable usable by Frisians: Grapevine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1408
msgid ""
"This grapevine is flowering. Honey can be produced from it by a beekeeper."
msgstr "Ši vynuogė žydi. Iš jo medų gali gaminti bitininkas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian warehouse: Headquarters
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1527
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Accommodation for your people. Also stores your wares and tools."
msgstr "apgyvendinimas jūsų žmonėms. Taip pat saugo jūsų prekes ir įrankius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian warehouse: Headquarters
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1529
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The headquarters is your main building."
msgstr "Būstinė yra jūsų pagrindinis pastatas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian warehouse: Warehouse
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1536
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Your workers and soldiers will find shelter here. Also stores your wares and"
" tools."
msgstr "Jūsų darbuotojai ir kariai čia ras prieglobstį. Taip pat saugo jūsų prekes ir įrankius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian warehouse: Port
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1543
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Serves as a base for overseas colonization and trade. Also stores your "
"soldiers, wares and tools."
msgstr "Tarnauja kaip užjūrio kolonizacijos ir prekybos bazė. Taip pat saugo jūsų karius, gaminius ir įrankius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian warehouse: Port
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1545
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Similar to the Headquarters a Port can be attacked and destroyed by an "
"enemy. It is recommendable to send soldiers to defend it."
msgstr "Panašiai kaip ir būstinė, uostą gali užpulti ir sunaikinti priešas. Rekomenduojama siųsti karius jo ginti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian market: Market
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1554
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Tradecraft is the fine art of getting others to give you the wares that you "
"want in exchange for wares you don’t want; excuse me, I mean, for wares you "
"convince them to think that they need."
msgstr "„Tradecraft“ yra puikus menas, leidžiantis kitiems duoti jums norimus gaminius mainais į prekes, kurių nenorite; Atsiprašau, aš turiu galvoje, dėl gaminių jūs įtikinate juos manyti, kad jiems reikia."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian market: Market
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1556
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A trader explaining his diplomacy"
msgstr "Prekybininkas, aiškinantis savo diplomatiją"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian market: Market
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1558
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A market enables trading with other tribes."
msgstr "Rinka leidžia prekiauti su kitomis gentimis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Quarry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1567
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "When I swing my pick, whole mountains fall before me!"
msgstr "Kai siūbuoju savo pasirinkimu, prieš mane krenta ištisi kalnai!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Quarry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1569
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A stonemason"
msgstr "akmentašis"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Quarry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1571
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Cuts raw pieces of granite out of rocks in the vicinity."
msgstr "Pjauna neapdorotus granito gabalus iš netoliese esančių uolų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Quarry
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1573
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The quarry needs rocks to cut within the work area."
msgstr "Karjerui reikia uolienų, kad būtų galima pjauti darbo zonoje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Quarry,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1576
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one granite between %1$s and %2$s, depending on "
"how far the stonemason has to walk."
msgstr "Iš šio pastato galima pagaminti vieną granitą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli turi nueiti akmentašys."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Quarry,
#. part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Woodcutter's House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Forester's
#. House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Hunter's
#. House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's
#. House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Clay Pit,
#. part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal
#. Burner's House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Berry
#. Farm, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Fruit
#. Collector's House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Beekeeper's House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Aqua Farm,
#. part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Scout's
#. House, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Ferry
#. Yard, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Shipyard,
#. part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1578
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1597
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1616
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1631
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1656
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1709
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1728
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1747
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1766
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1785
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1804
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1822
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2283
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2306
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "In case of slopes or obstacles in the way, the time is increased."
msgstr "Esant šlaitams ar kelyje esančioms kliūtims, laikas pailgėja."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Woodcutter's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1586
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"I cannot see a tree without imagining what it would look like in terms of "
"furniture."
msgstr "Negaliu matyti medžio neįsivaizduodamas, kaip jis atrodytų baldų atžvilgiu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Woodcutter's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1588
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "An over-enthusiastic woodcutter"
msgstr "Pernelyg entuziastingas medžio kirtėjas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Woodcutter's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1592
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The woodcutter’s house needs trees to fell within the work area."
msgstr "Medienos namui reikia medžių, kad jie įkristų į darbo zoną."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Woodcutter's House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1595
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one log between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the woodcutter has to walk."
msgstr "Šis pastatas gali pagaminti vieną rąstą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli turi nueiti miško kirtėjas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Forester's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1605
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"What can ever be more beautiful than the brilliant sun’s beams shining "
"through the glistering canopy of leaves?"
msgstr "Kas gali būti gražesnė už nuostabius saulės spindulius, šviečiančius pro blizgantį lapų baldakimą?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Forester's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1607
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A forester explaining his choice of profession"
msgstr "Miškininkas, paaiškinantis savo profesijos pasirinkimą"

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Forester's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1611
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The forester’s house needs free space within the work area to plant the "
"trees."
msgstr "Miškininko namams darbo zonoje reikia laisvos vietos medžiams sodinti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Forester's
#. House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1614
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The forester plants one tree between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how far he "
"has to walk."
msgstr "Miškininkas pasodina vieną medį nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Hunter's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1626
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The hunter’s house needs animals to hunt within the work area."
msgstr "Medžiotojų namams reikia gyvūnų, kad galėtų medžioti darbo zonoje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Hunter's
#. House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1629
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one meat between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the hunter has to walk."
msgstr "Šiame pastate galima pagaminti vieną mėsą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek medžiotojas turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Hunter's
#. House, part 3
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1633
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The hunter produces one fur after he has produced five pieces of meat."
msgstr "Pagaminęs penkis mėsos gabalus, medžiotojas užaugina vieną kailį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1641
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Hunters can’t sell anything on a Friday, but fishers don’t have such "
"problems."
msgstr "Penktadienį medžiotojai nieko negali parduoti, bet žvejai tokių problemų neturi."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1643
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A hunter admiring a fisher"
msgstr "Medžiotojas žavisi žveju"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1645
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Fishes on the coast near the fisher’s house."
msgstr "Žuvys pakrantėje prie žvejo namų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's House,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1648
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The fisher’s house needs water full of fish within the work area."
msgstr "Žvejo namams darbo zonoje reikia vandens, pilno žuvų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's House,
#. part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1650
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Roads and trees along the shoreline block fishing."
msgstr "Keliai ir medžiai palei kranto liniją blokuoja žvejybą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Fisher's
#. House, part 1
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Aqua Farm,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1654
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1802
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one fish between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the fisher has to walk."
msgstr "Šiame pastate galima užauginti vieną žuvį nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek žvejo turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Reed Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1664
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"No worse fortune can befall a reed farmer than to see his roof leaking."
msgstr "Nendrių augintojui negali ištikti blogesnis turtas, kaip matyti, kaip jo stogas nesandari."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Reed Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1666
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Anonymous reed farmer"
msgstr "Anoniminis nendrių augintojas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Reed Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1668
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Cultivates reed that serves three different purposes for the Frisians."
msgstr "Augina nendres, kurios fryzams tarnauja trims skirtingiems tikslams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Reed Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1670
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Reed is the traditional material for roofing. It is also needed to produce "
"baskets and fishing nets, and it is woven – together with reindeer fur – "
"into the cloth used for ships’ sails."
msgstr "Nendrė yra tradicinė stogo dengimo medžiaga. Jis taip pat reikalingas krepšiams ir žvejybos tinklams gaminti, o kartu su šiaurės elnio kailiu jis įaustas į laivų burėms naudojamą audinį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Reed Farm,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1673
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The reed farmer sows and harvests one sheaf of reed between %1$s and %2$s, "
"depending on how far he has to walk."
msgstr "Nendrių augintojas sėja ir nuima vieną nendrių pluoštą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Reed Farm,
#. part 2; %s is replaced by 'N growing fields'
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1675
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The reed farm needs at least %s to work at full productivity most of the "
"time."
msgstr "Nendrių ūkiui reikia bent %s, kad didžiąją laiko dalį dirbtų visu produktyvumu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Well
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1683
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "We love the sea so much that we don’t want to drink it empty!"
msgstr "Mums taip patinka jūra, kad nenorime jos gerti tuščio!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Well
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1685
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Chieftain Arldor’s retort when he was asked why his tribe can’t drink salt "
"water"
msgstr "Vyriausiojo Arldoro replika, kai jo paklausė, kodėl jo gentis negali gerti sūraus vandens"

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Well, part
#. 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1690
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The carrier needs %s to get one bucket full of water."
msgstr "Vežėjui reikia %s, kad vienas kibiras būtų pilnas vandens."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Well, part
#. 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1692
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "If the water resource is depleted, the carrier needs %s on average."
msgstr "Jei vandens ištekliai išeikvoti, vežėjui vidutiniškai reikia %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Clay Pit
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1700
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "You think you can build a house without my help?"
msgstr "Manote, kad galite pastatyti namą be mano pagalbos?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Clay Pit
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1702
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A clay digger arguing with a builder"
msgstr "Molio kasėjas ginčijasi su statybininku"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Clay Pit
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1704
msgctxt "building"
msgid ""
"Digs up mud from the ground and uses water to turn it into clay. Clay is "
"used to make bricks, reinforce the charcoal kiln and to build ships."
msgstr "Kasa purvą nuo žemės ir naudoja vandenį, kad jį paverstų moliu. Molis naudojamas plytoms gaminti, anglies krosniui sutvirtinti ir laivams statyti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Clay Pit,
#. part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1707
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one clay between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the clay digger has to walk."
msgstr "Šiame pastate galima pagaminti vieną molį nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli molio kasėjas turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal Burner's
#. House
#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1717
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1936
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"No other tribe has ever mastered the art of charcoal burning as we have!"
msgstr "Jokia kita gentis niekada neįvaldė anglies deginimo meno, kaip mes!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal
#. Burner's House
#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal
#. Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1719
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1938
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The inventor of the Frisian charcoal kiln"
msgstr "Fryzų anglies krosnies išradėjas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal Burner's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1723
msgctxt "building"
msgid ""
"The charcoal burner’s house needs holes in the ground that were dug by a "
"clay pit’s worker nearby to erect charcoal stacks in them."
msgstr "Anglies degiklio namui žemėje reikia skylių, kurias iškasė netoliese esantis molio duobės darbuotojas, kad juose būtų galima pastatyti anglies rietuves."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal
#. Burner's House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1726
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"This building can produce one coal between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how "
"far the charcoal burner has to walk."
msgstr "Šis pastatas gali pagaminti vieną anglį nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli turi nueiti anglies degiklis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Berry Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1736
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"My bushes may not be as tall as your trees, but I don’t know anybody who "
"likes to eat bark!"
msgstr "Mano krūmai gali būti ne tokie aukšti kaip jūsų medžiai, bet aš nepažįstu nė vieno, kuris mėgsta valgyti žievę!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Berry Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1738
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A berry farmer to a forester"
msgstr "Uogų augintojas miškininkui"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Berry Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1740
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Plants berry bushes in the surrounding area."
msgstr "Apylinkėse sodina uogų krūmus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Berry Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1742
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The berry farm needs free space within the work area to plant the bushes."
msgstr "Uogų ūkiui darbo zonoje reikia laisvos vietos krūmams apsodinti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Berry
#. Farm, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1745
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The berry farmer plants one bush between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how far"
" he has to walk."
msgstr "Uogų augintojas pasodina vieną krūmą tarp %1$s ir %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Fruit Collector's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1755
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Meat doesn’t grow on bushes. Fruit does."
msgstr "Mėsa neauga ant krūmų. Vaisiai daro."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Fruit
#. Collector's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1757
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A fruit collector advertising his harvest to a landlady"
msgstr "vaisių kolekcionierius, reklamuojantis savo derlių šeimininkei"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Fruit
#. Collector's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1759
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Collects berries from nearby bushes."
msgstr "Surenka uogas iš netoliese esančių krūmų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Fruit Collector's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1761
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The fruit collector needs bushes full of berries within the work area."
msgstr "Vaisių kolekcionieriui darbo zonoje reikia krūmų, pilnų uogų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Fruit
#. Collector's House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1764
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The fruit collector harvests one bush between %1$s and %2$s, depending on "
"how far he has to walk."
msgstr "Vaisių kolekcionierius nuima vieną krūmą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Beekeeper's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1774
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If my honey tastes bitter, I must have left some bee stings in it. There are"
" never any bee stings in my honey, therefore, it is not bitter."
msgstr "Jei mano medaus skonis kartaus, turbūt palikau jame keletą bičių įgėlimų. Mano meduje niekada nėra bičių įgėlimų, todėl jis nėra kartaus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Beekeeper's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1776
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A beekeeper ignoring a customer’s complaint"
msgstr "bitininkas, ignoruojantis kliento skundą"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Beekeeper's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1778
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Keeps bees and lets them swarm over flowering fields to produce honey."
msgstr "Laiko bites ir leidžia joms spiečiusi virš žydinčių laukų, kad gautų medų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Beekeeper's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1780
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Needs medium-sized fields (barley, wheat, reed, corn or blackroot) or bushes"
" (berry bushes or grapevines) nearby."
msgstr "Reikia vidutinio dydžio laukų (miežių, kviečių, nendrių, kukurūzų ar juodųjų šaknų) arba krūmų (uogų krūmų ar vynuogių)."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Beekeeper's House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1783
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The beekeeper collects one honey between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how far"
" he has to walk."
msgstr "Bitininkas surenka vieną medų nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Aqua Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1793
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Why on earth shouldn’t we be able to catch fish even in the desert?"
msgstr "Kodėl, po velnių, neturėtume galėti gaudyti žuvies net dykumoje?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Aqua Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1795
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The fisherman who invented aqua farming"
msgstr "Žvejas, išradęs vandens auginimą"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Aqua Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1797
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Breeds fish as food for soldiers and miners."
msgstr "Veisia žuvis kaip maistą kareiviams ir kalnakasiams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Aqua Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1799
msgctxt "building"
msgid ""
"The aqua farm needs holes in the ground that were dug by a clay pit’s worker"
" nearby to use as fishing ponds."
msgstr "Vandens ūkiui reikia skylių žemėje, kurias iškasė netoliese esantis molio duobės darbuotojas, kad galėtų naudoti kaip žvejybos tvenkinius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Scout's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1812
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Everyone has their own ideas on how exactly we should explore the enemy’s "
"territory… One more ‘improvement’ suggestion and we’ll demand meals instead "
"of rations!"
msgstr "Kiekvienas turi savo idėjų, kaip tiksliai turėtume tyrinėti priešo teritoriją... dar vienas „patobulinimo“ pasiūlymas ir mes reikalausime patiekalų, o ne davinio!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Scout's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1814
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The spokesman of the scouts’ labor union"
msgstr "skautų profesinės sąjungos atstovas"

#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1815
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"You need to connect this flag to a scout’s house before you can send a scout"
" here."
msgstr "Turite prijungti šią vėliavą prie skautų namų, kad galėtumėte čia išsiųsti skautą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Scout's
#. House, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1820
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "One exploration trip of the scout takes between %1$s and %2$s."
msgstr "Viena žvalgo kelionė trunka nuo %1$s iki %2$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Brick Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1832
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If there is not enough coal, only the most foolish of leaders would deprive "
"his brick kilns of it first."
msgstr "Jei nėra pakankamai anglies, tik patys kvailiausi lyderiai pirmiausia atimtų iš jo plytų krosnis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Brick Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1834
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A brickmaker arguing with his chieftain who was doing just that"
msgstr "plytų gamintojas ginčijasi su savo viršininku, kuris tai darė"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Brick Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1836
msgctxt "building"
msgid ""
"Burns bricks using granite and clay, and coal as fuel. Bricks are the most "
"important building material."
msgstr "Degina plytas naudojant granitą ir molį, o anglį kaip kurą. Plytos yra svarbiausia statybinė medžiaga."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Brick Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1838
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The brick kiln needs %s on average to produce one brick."
msgstr "Plytų krosnyje vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad būtų pagaminta viena plyta."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Furnace
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1845
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Miners get ores from the depths of the hills; but without our work, their "
"labour is in vain."
msgstr "Kalnakasiai gauna rūdas iš kalvų gelmių; Bet be mūsų darbo jų darbas bergždžias."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Furnace
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1847
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Slogan of the Smelters’ Guild"
msgstr "Smeltėjų gildijos šūkis"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Furnace
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1849
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Smelts iron ore and gold ore into iron and gold ingots using coal."
msgstr "Iš geležies lydos geležies ir aukso rūdos į geležies ir aukso luitus, naudojant anglį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Furnace
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1851
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all metals are needed by the economy,"
" production of one iron takes %1$s and one gold takes %2$s on average. If "
"only one kind of metal is needed by the economy, production of one iron "
"takes %3$s and one gold takes %4$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas ir visi metalai reikalingi ekonomikai, vienos geležies gamyba užtrunka %1$s, o vienas auksas – vidutiniškai %2$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies metalo, vienos geležies gamyba užtrunka %3$s, o vienam auksui – vidutiniškai %4$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Recycling Center
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1858
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Of course these weapons could be used by other soldiers again without being "
"smelted down first! The only drawback is that they’d break in two at the "
"first blow."
msgstr "Žinoma, šiuos ginklus vėl galėtų panaudoti kiti kariai, prieš tai neišlydę! Vienintelis trūkumas yra tas, kad po pirmojo smūgio jie lūžtų į dvi dalis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Recycling
#. Center
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1860
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A smelter explaining the need for recycling to his impatient chieftain"
msgstr "lydykla, paaiškinanti, kad reikia perdirbti savo nekantraujančiam vadovui"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Recycling
#. Center
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1862
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Recycles old armor and weapon parts that have been discarded by training "
"sites into fur, iron and gold."
msgstr "Perdirba senus šarvus ir ginklų dalis, kurias mokymo aikštelės išmetė į kailį, geležį ir auksą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Recycling
#. Center
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1864
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all materials are needed by the "
"economy, production of one fur takes %1$s, one iron takes %2$s and one gold "
"takes %3$s on average. If only one kind of material is needed by the "
"economy, production of one fur takes %4$s, one iron takes %5$s and one gold "
"takes %6$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra pilnai aprūpintas ir visos medžiagos reikalingos ekonomikai, vieno kailio gamyba užtrunka %1$s, viena lygintuvas užtrunka %2$s, o vienas auksas – vidutiniškai %3$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies medžiagos, vieno kailio gamyba užtrunka %4$s, viena lygintuvas – %5$s, o vienas auksas – vidutiniškai %6$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Blacksmithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1871
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "If you don’t have iron, change your name from blacksmith to lacksmith!"
msgstr "Jei neturite geležies, pakeiskite savo vardą iš Blacksmith į Lacksmith!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Blacksmithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1873
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Irritated chieftain during a metal shortage"
msgstr "susierzinęs vadas metalo trūkumo metu"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Blacksmithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1875
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Forges tools to equip new workers."
msgstr "Kaltina įrankius naujiems darbuotojams aprūpinti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site:
#. Blacksmithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1877
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all tools are needed by the economy, "
"production of one of each tool takes %1$s on average. If only one kind of "
"tool is needed by the economy, its production takes %2$s on average. Needles"
" are an exception – in the time to produce one tool two needles are "
"produced."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas ir visi įrankiai reikalingi ekonomikai, vieno iš kiekvieno įrankio gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %1$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies įrankio, jos gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %2$s. Adatos yra išimtis – per vieną įrankį pagaminti vieną įrankį gaminamos dvi adatos."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Small Armor
#. Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1884
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"I don’t forge swords because soldiers need ’em, but soldiers get ’em because"
" I forge ’em."
msgstr "Aš nekaltu kardų, nes kariams jų reikia, bet kareiviai juos gauna, nes aš juos kalsiu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Small
#. Armor Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1886
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A blacksmith pointing out his influence on soldier training"
msgstr "kalvis, nurodantis savo įtaką kario mokymui"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Small Armor
#. Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1888
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Produces basic weapons and helmets for the soldiers."
msgstr "Gamina pagrindinius ginklus ir šalmus kariams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Small
#. Armor Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1890
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all swords and helmets are needed by "
"the economy, production of one short sword takes %1$s, one long sword takes "
"%2$s and one helmet takes %3$s on average. If only one kind of sword or "
"helmet is needed by the economy, production of one short sword takes %4$s, "
"one long sword takes %5$s and one helmet takes %6$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas ir visi kardai bei šalmai reikalingi ekonomikai, vieno trumpo kardo gamybai reikia %1$s, vienam ilgam kardui reikia %2$s, o vienam šalmui – vidutiniškai %3$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies kardo ar šalmo, vieno trumpo kardo gamybai reikia %4$s, vienam ilgam kardui reikia %5$s, o vienam šalmui – vidutiniškai %6$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Large Armor
#. Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1897
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Of course I could still forge short and long swords, but it is beneath my "
"honor to bother with such basic equipment now."
msgstr "Žinoma, vis tiek galėčiau padirbti trumpus ir ilgus kardus, bet dabar man be garbės vargti su tokia pagrindine įranga."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Large
#. Armor Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1899
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"A master blacksmith refusing to forge anything but the most sophisticated "
"helmets and weapons"
msgstr "Meistras kalvis atsisako padirbti ką nors, išskyrus pačius sudėtingiausius šalmus ir ginklus"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Large Armor
#. Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1901
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Produces advanced weapons and golden helmets for the soldiers."
msgstr "Gamina pažangius ginklus ir auksinius šalmus kariams."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Large
#. Armor Smithy
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1903
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all swords and helmets are needed by "
"the economy, production of one broadsword takes %1$s, one double-edged sword"
" takes %2$s and one golden helmet takes %3$s on average. If only one kind of"
" sword or helmet is needed by the economy, production of one broadsword "
"takes %4$s, one double-edged sword takes %5$s and one golden helmet takes "
"%6$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra pilnai aprūpintas, o ekonomikai reikia visų kardų ir šalmų, vieno plataus kardo gamybai reikia %1$s, vienam dviašmeniui kardui reikia %2$s, o vienam auksiniam šalmui – vidutiniškai %3$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies kardo ar šalmo, vieno plataus kardo gamybai reikia %4$s, vienam dviašmeniui kardui reikia %5$s, o vienam auksiniam šalmui – vidutiniškai %6$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Sewing Room
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1910
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"You soldiers think a good sword is everything, but where would you be if you"
" had no garments?"
msgstr "Jūs, kareiviai, manote, kad geras kardas yra viskas, bet kur būtumėte, jei neturėtumėte drabužių?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Sewing
#. Room
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1912
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A seamstress scolding a soldier for disrespecting her profession"
msgstr "Siuvėja bara kareivį už nepagarbą savo profesijai"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Sewing Room
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1914
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Sews fur garments out of reindeer fur."
msgstr "Iš šiaurės elnio kailio siuva kailinius drabužius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Sewing
#. Room
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1916
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The sewing room needs %s on average to produce one fur garment."
msgstr "Siuvimo kambariui vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad būtų pagamintas vienas kailinis drabužis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Tailor's Shop
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1923
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Don’t complain if these garments are too heavy – they’re not supposed to be "
"light but to keep you alive a bit longer!"
msgstr "Nesiskundykite, jei šie drabužiai yra per sunkūs – jie neturėtų būti lengvi, o ilgiau išlaikyti jus gyvą!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Tailor's
#. Shop
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1925
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A trainer scolding a soldier"
msgstr "Treneris bara kareivį"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Tailor's Shop
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1927
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Equips fur garments with iron or gold to produce good armor."
msgstr "Įrengia kailinius drabužius geležimi arba auksu, kad būtų sukurti geri šarvai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Tailor's
#. Shop
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1929
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all garments are needed by the "
"economy, production of one of each garment takes %1$s on average. If only "
"one kind of garment is needed by the economy, its production takes %2$s on "
"average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas ir visi drabužiai reikalingi ekonomikai, vieno iš kiekvieno drabužio gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %1$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies drabužio, jo gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %2$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Charcoal
#. Kiln
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1942
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The charcoal kiln needs %s on average to produce one coal."
msgstr "Anglies krosnyje vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad būtų pagaminta viena anglis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Smokery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1949
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Miners and soldiers are so picky… But who am I to complain, as I make my "
"living from it?"
msgstr "Kalnakasiai ir kareiviai yra tokie išrankūs... bet kam aš toks, kad skųsčiau, nes iš to užsidirbu?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Smokery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1951
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A smoker explaining his profession"
msgstr "rūkalius, paaiškinantis savo profesiją"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Smokery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1953
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Smokes fish and meat using logs. Only smoked meat and fish are good enough "
"to be eaten by miners and soldiers."
msgstr "Rūko žuvį ir mėsą naudodamas rąstus. Tik rūkyta mėsa ir žuvis yra pakankamai geri, kad juos valgytų kalnakasiai ir kareiviai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Smokery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1955
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied, production of one of each smoked food "
"takes %s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas, vieno iš kiekvieno rūkyto maisto gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1962
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Why shouldn’t my bread taste good? It’s only barley and water!"
msgstr "Kodėl mano duona neturėtų būti skanus? Tai tik miežiai ir vanduo!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1964
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A baker"
msgstr "kepėjas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1966
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Bakes bread out of barley and water to feed miners and soldiers."
msgstr "Kepa duoną iš miežių ir vandens, kad pamaitintų kalnakasius ir kareivius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1968
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The bakery needs %s on average to produce one loaf of bread."
msgstr "Kepyklai vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad pagamintų vieną duonos kepalą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Honey Bread
#. Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1975
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Rookies will say that vengeance is sweet. Heroes will say that honey bread "
"is sweeter."
msgstr "Naujokai sakys, kad kerštas yra saldus. Herojai sakys, kad medaus duona saldesnė."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Honey
#. Bread Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1977
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A trainer in conversation with a baker"
msgstr "Treneris pokalbyje su kepėju"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Honey Bread
#. Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1979
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Bakes honey bread out of barley, water and honey to feed miners in deep "
"mines and soldiers in advanced training."
msgstr "Kepa medaus duoną iš miežių, vandenį ir medų, kad maitintų kalnakasius giliose kasyklose ir karius pažangiuose mokymuose."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Honey
#. Bread Bakery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1981
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all breads are needed by the economy,"
" production of one bread takes %1$s and one honey bread takes %2$s on "
"average. If only one kind of bread is needed by the economy, production of "
"one bread or one honey bread takes %3$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas ir visa duona reikalinga ekonomikai, vienos duonos gamyba užtrunka %1$s, o viena medaus duona vidutiniškai užtrunka %2$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies duonos, vienos duonos ar vienos medaus duonos gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %3$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1988
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"I know no single master miner who’ll ever work without a nice pint of beer!"
msgstr "Nepažįstu nė vieno meistro, kuris kada nors dirbtų be gražaus puslitros alaus!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1990
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A brewer boasting about the importance of his profession"
msgstr "Aludaris giriasi savo profesijos svarba"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1992
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Brews beer for miners and soldier training."
msgstr "Paruošia alų kalnakasiams ir karių mokymui."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:1994
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The brewery needs %s on average to brew one mug of beer."
msgstr "Alaus daryklai vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad išvirtų vieną puodelį alaus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Mead Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2001
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "If you like beer, you’ve never tasted mead."
msgstr "Jei mėgstate alų, niekada neragavote midaus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Mead
#. Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2003
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Slogan over a mead brewery"
msgstr "Šūkis virš midaus alaus daryklos"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Mead Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2005
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Brews beer out of barley and water. It also brews mead, which is beer "
"refined with honey. Mead is consumed by experienced soldiers."
msgstr "verda alų iš miežių ir vandens. Taip pat verda midaus, kuris yra rafinuotas su medumi. Midus vartoja patyrę kariai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Mead
#. Brewery
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2007
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all drinks are needed by the economy,"
" production of one beer takes %1$s and one mead takes %2$s on average. If "
"only one kind of drink is needed by the economy, production of one beer or "
"one mead takes %3$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra pilnai aprūpintas ir visi gėrimai reikalingi ekonomikai, vieno alaus gamyba užtrunka %1$s, o vienam midui – vidutiniškai %2$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies gėrimo, vieno alaus ar vieno midaus gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %3$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Tavern
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2014
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Nothing but fruit all day… Couldn’t you hurry up a bit?"
msgstr "Nieko, išskyrus vaisius visą dieną... ar negalėjai šiek tiek paskubėti?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Tavern
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2016
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Hungry customers in times of a shortage of smoked fish and meat"
msgstr "Išalkę klientai rūkytos žuvies ir mėsos trūkumo laikais"

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Tavern
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2020
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the tavern is fully supplied, it can produce one ration in %1$s on "
"average, using two kinds of ingredients. If it can only use one kind of "
"ingredient, it can produce one ration in %2$s on average."
msgstr "Jei taverna yra pilnai aprūpinta, ji gali pagaminti vidutiniškai vieną racioną %1$s, naudojant dviejų rūšių ingredientus. Jei jis gali naudoti tik vienos rūšies ingredientus, jis gali pagaminti vidutiniškai vieną racioną %2$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Drinking Hall
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2027
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"All I need to be happy is a slice of honey bread with some smoked meat and a"
" beer."
msgstr "Viskas, ko man reikia, kad būčiau laiminga, yra riekelė medaus duonos su rūkyta mėsa ir alumi."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Drinking
#. Hall
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2029
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A master miner to the landlady"
msgstr "Meistras kalnakasys šeimininkei"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Drinking Hall
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2031
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Prepares rations for scouts and rations and meals to feed the miners in all "
"mines."
msgstr "Ruošia skautų ir racionų racioną bei valgį, kad pamaitintų kalnakasius visose kasyklose."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Drinking
#. Hall
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2033
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and all kinds of food are needed by the "
"economy, production of one of each food takes %1$s on average. If only one "
"kind of food is needed by the economy, production of one ration takes %2$s "
"and one meal takes %3$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra pilnai aprūpintas ir ekonomikai reikia visų rūšių maisto, vieno iš kiekvieno maisto gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %1$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik vienos rūšies maisto, vieno raciono gamyba užtrunka %2$s, o vienas patiekalas – vidutiniškai %3$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Barracks
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2040
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"You have thirty seconds to learn the basics of swordfighting and how to stay"
" alive in battle. A third of that time has gone by for the introduction "
"alone! You’d better pay close attention to me in order to make the most of "
"it. Now here is your new short sword, forged just for you by our best "
"blacksmiths. Time’s up everyone, now go occupy your sentinels!"
msgstr "Turite trisdešimt sekundžių, kad išmoktumėte kovos su kardais pagrindus ir kaip išlikti gyvam mūšyje. Trečdalis to laiko praėjo vien įžangai! Geriau atkreipkite į mane didelį dėmesį, kad išnaudotumėte visas galimybes. Dabar čia yra jūsų naujas trumpas kardas, kurį padirbo tik jums geriausi mūsų kalviai. Laikas visiems baigėsi, dabar eik užimk savo sargybinius!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Barracks
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2042
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A trainer greeting the new recruits"
msgstr "Treneris sveikina naujus darbuotojus"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Barracks
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2044
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Equips recruits and trains them as soldiers."
msgstr "aprūpina juos ir apmoko juos kaip karius."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Barracks
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2046
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The barracks need %s on average to recruit one soldier."
msgstr "Kareivams vidutiniškai reikia %s, kad įdarbintų vieną karį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Reindeer Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2055
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Who says a beast of burden cannot be useful for other things than transport?"
msgstr "Kas sako, kad žvėris naštos negali būti naudingas kitiems dalykams, išskyrus transportą?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Reindeer
#. Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2057
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The reindeer breeder who first proposed using reindeer fur for clothing"
msgstr "šiaurės elnių veisėjas, kuris pirmasis pasiūlė drabužiams naudoti šiaurės elnių kailį"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Reindeer Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2059
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Breeds strong reindeer for adding them to the transportation system. Also "
"keeps them for their fur, which is turned into armor and cloth."
msgstr "Veisia stiprius šiaurės elnius, kad įtrauktų juos į transportavimo sistemą. Taip pat laiko juos kailiui, kuris paverčiamas šarvais ir audiniais."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Reindeer Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2061
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the supply is steady and there is continuous demand for fur, then the "
"reindeer farm produces one meat after producing three pieces of fur."
msgstr "Jei pasiūla yra pastovi ir nuolat yra kailio paklausa, tai šiaurės elnių ūkis, pagaminęs tris kailio gabalus, išaugina vieną mėsą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Reindeer
#. Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2063
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied and both reindeers and furs are needed by"
" the economy, production of one reindeer takes %1$s and one fur takes %2$s "
"on average. If only reindeers are needed by the economy, their production "
"takes %3$s on average. If only fur is needed by the economy, its production "
"takes %4$s on average."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra pilnai aprūpintas ir ekonomikai reikia ir elnių, ir kailių, vieno šiaurės elnio gamyba užtrunka %1$s, o vienam kailiui – vidutiniškai %2$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik šiaurės elnių, jų produkcija vidutiniškai užtrunka %3$s. Jei ekonomikai reikia tik kailio, jo gamyba vidutiniškai užtrunka %4$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian production site: Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2070
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"No frost, no heat; no rain, no drought; no rats, no locusts; naught can "
"destroy my harvest."
msgstr "Jokio šalčio, jokio karščio; Jokio lietaus, jokios sausros; Jokių žiurkių, jokių skėrių; Niekas negali sunaikinti mano derliaus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian production site: Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2072
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"A farmer’s reply when asked by his chieftain why he was planting such a "
"slow-growing grain."
msgstr "Ūkininko atsakymas, kai jo vadas paklausė, kodėl jis sodino tokį lėtai augantį grūdą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2074
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Sows and harvests barley."
msgstr "Sėja ir nuima miežių derlių."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Farm
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2076
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "The farm needs free space within the work area to plant seeds."
msgstr "Ūkiui reikia laisvos vietos darbo zonoje sėkloms sodinti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Farm, part
#. 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2079
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The farmer sows and harvests one sheaf of barley between %1$s and %2$s, "
"depending on how far he has to walk."
msgstr "Ūkininkas sėja ir nuima vieną miežių pluoštą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Farm, part
#. 2; %s is replaced by 'N growing fields'
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2081
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The farm needs at least %s to work at full productivity most of the time."
msgstr "Ūkiui reikia bent %s, kad didžiąją laiko dalį dirbtų visu produktyvumu."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Diker's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2089
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Constructs breakwaters nearby to gain new land from the sea."
msgstr "Netoliese stato bangolaužius, kad gautų naują žemę iš jūros."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian production site: Diker's House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2091
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"The diker will terraform the land around each breakwater he builds several "
"times. You can manually remove breakwaters when the land is sufficiently "
"secured to prevent wasting resources; to do so, build a flag, road, or "
"building in the dike’s place."
msgstr "Dikeris kelis kartus suformuos žemę aplink kiekvieną savo pastatytą molą. Galite rankiniu būdu pašalinti bangolaužius, kai žemė yra pakankamai apsaugota, kad būtų išvengta išteklių švaistymo; Norėdami tai padaryti, pylimo vietoje pastatykite vėliavą, kelią ar pastatą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Diker's
#. House
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2093
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If this building is fully supplied, the diker can perform one terraform "
"between %1$s and %2$s, depending on how far he has to walk."
msgstr "Jei šis pastatas yra visiškai aprūpintas, Diker gali atlikti vieną teraformą nuo %1$s iki %2$s, priklausomai nuo to, kiek toli jis turi nueiti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Rock Mine
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian production site: Deep Rock Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2102
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2111
msgctxt "building"
msgid "Digs granite out of the ground in mountain terrain."
msgstr "Kasa granitą iš žemės kalnų vietovėje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Rock Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2104
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the rock mine can produce granite in %s on "
"average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, uolienų kasykla gali gaminti granitą vidutiniškai %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Deep Rock
#. Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2113
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the deep rock mine can produce granite in %s "
"on average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, giliųjų uolienų kasykla gali gaminti vidutiniškai %s granitą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Coal Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2122
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the coal mine can produce coal in %s on "
"average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, anglies kasykla gali gaminti anglį vidutiniškai %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Deep Coal
#. Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2131
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the deep coal mine can produce coal in %s on "
"average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, giliųjų anglių kasykla gali gaminti anglį vidutiniškai %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Iron Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2140
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the iron mine can produce one piece of iron "
"ore in %s on average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, geležies kasykloje vidutiniškai galima pagaminti vieną geležies rūdos gabalą %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Deep Iron
#. Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2149
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the deep iron mine can produce iron ore in %s "
"on average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, giliosios geležies kasyklos gali gaminti vidutiniškai %s geležies rūdos."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Gold Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2158
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the gold mine can produce one piece of gold "
"ore in %s on average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, aukso kasykla gali pagaminti vidutiniškai vieną aukso rūdos gabalą %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian production site: Deep Gold
#. Mine
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2167
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If the food supply is steady, the deep gold mine can produce gold ore in %s "
"on average."
msgstr "Jei maisto tiekimas yra pastovus, gilioji aukso kasykla gali gaminti aukso rūdą %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian training site: Training Camp
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2176
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Just be quiet, listen carefully, and do try not to stab yourself until I’ve "
"explained to you how to hold a broadsword."
msgstr "Tiesiog tylėkite, atidžiai klausykite ir stenkitės nedurti savęs, kol nepaaiškinsiu, kaip laikyti platųjį kardą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian training site: Training
#. Camp
#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Frisian training site: Training
#. Arena
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2178
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2197
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "A trainer training a soldier"
msgstr "Treneris, mokantis karį"

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian training site: Training Camp
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2180
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Trains soldiers in Attack up to level 3 as well as in Defense and Health to "
"level 1. Equips the soldiers with all necessary weapons and armor parts."
msgstr "Apmoko karius puolime iki 3 lygio, taip pat gynybos ir sveikatos iki 1 lygio. Aprūpina karius visais reikalingais ginklais ir šarvų dalimis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian training site: Training Camp
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2182
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Frisian soldiers cannot train in Evade and will remain at their initial "
"level."
msgstr "Fryzų kariai negali treniruotis išsisukinėti ir išliks pradiniame lygyje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian training site: Training
#. Camp, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2185
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If all needed wares are delivered in time, a training camp can train one "
"soldier one level in attack, defense or health in %s on average."
msgstr "Jei visi reikalingi gaminiai pristatomi laiku, treniruočių stovykla gali išmokyti vieną karį vieno lygio puolimo, gynybos ar sveikatos vidutiniu %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian training site: Training
#. Camp, part 2
#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian training site: Training
#. Arena, part 2
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2187
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2206
#, lua-format
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Complete training of one soldier takes %s on average."
msgstr "Visiškas vieno kario mokymas vidutiniškai užtrunka %s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Frisian training site: Training Arena
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2195
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Now that you have two swords, there’s more of a risk you’ll accidentally "
"stab yourself, but if you got this far, you’ll likely master this challenge "
"as well."
msgstr "Dabar, kai turite du kardus, yra didesnė rizika, kad netyčia įdursite save, bet jei pasieksite taip toli, greičiausiai taip pat įveiksite šį iššūkį."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian training site: Training Arena
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2199
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Trains soldiers in Attack, Defense and Health to the final level. Equips the"
" soldiers with all necessary weapons and armor parts."
msgstr "Apmoko karius puolime, gynyboje ir sveikatą iki galutinio lygio. aprūpina karius visais reikalingais ginklais ir šarvų dalimis."

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Frisian training site: Training Arena
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2201
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"Trains only soldiers who have been trained to the maximum level by the "
"Training Camp."
msgstr "Treniruoja tik karius, kurie buvo apmokyti iki maksimalaus lygio treniruočių stovykloje."

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Frisian training site: Training
#. Arena, part 1
#: ../../../../data/tribes/initialization/frisians/units.lua:2204
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid ""
"If all needed wares are delivered in time, a training arena can train one "
"soldier one level in attack in %1$s, one level in defense in %2$s and one "
"level in health in %3$s on average."
msgstr "Jei visi reikalingi gaminiai pristatomi laiku, treniruočių arena gali treniruoti vieną kareivį vieną lygį puolime %1$s, vieną gynybos lygį %2$s ir vieną sveikatos lygį vidutiniškai %3$s."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian military site: Wooden Tower
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian military site: High Wooden
#. Tower
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian military site: Sentinel
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian military site: Outpost
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian military site: Tower
#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for a Frisian military site: Fortress
